08/12/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Rating agency Standard & Poors announced on Monday (December 7th) it has put Greece on a negative credit watch amid fears that its deteriorating public finances might impact its growing debts. Greece's debts currently amount to over 110% of its GDP. Finance Minister George Papaconstantinou has said the government will work to correct its "lack of credibility" in the financial markets. (BBC, Wall Street Journal - 07/12/09)
